what is shingles my dad has shingles what is it how can i help him feel better if anything p s i am so don't use big scientific words shingles is a disease caused by the varicella zoster virus the same virus that causes chickenpox after you have chickenpox the virus stays in your body it may not cause problems for many years as you get older the virus may reappear as shingles unlike chickenpox you can't catch shingles from someone who has it early signs of shingles include burning or shooting pain and tingling or itching usually on one side of the body or face the pain can be mild to severe blisters then form and last from one to days if shingles appears on your face it may affect your vision or hearing the pain of shingles may last for weeks months or even years after the blisters have healed there is no cure for shingles early treatment with medicines that fight the virus may help these medicines may also help prevent lingering pain a vaccine may prevent shingles or lessen its effects the vaccine is for people or over who have had chickenpox but who have not had shingles Chickenpox Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Herpes simplex virus Cytomegalovirus Psoriasis Common cold Smallpox Pneumonia Autism Cancer Varicella zoster virus Group A streptococcal infection Vaccine AIDS Hepatitis C Traumatic brain injury Medicine Stomach cancer Chronic fatigue syndrome Eczema Influenza Ebola Sexually-transmitted infection Rabies Malaria Prostate cancer Cellulitis Lyme disease Conjunctivitis Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Hepatitis Measles Mouth ulcer Marburg virus Church of Christ, Scientist Homeopathy Avian influenza Paget's disease of bone Carpal tunnel syndrome Rubella Acne Mumps Stroke Virus Neuralgia Anthrax Syphilis Allergy Diarrhea Leukemia Foot-and-mouth disease Yellow fever HIV vaccine Autoimmune diseases Louis Pasteur Scar Infectious mononucleosis Decompression sickness Antiviral drug Bell's palsy Stuttering Cirrhosis Natural Hygiene Fibromyalgia Diabetes mellitus Sickle-cell 